cause.description:
Your contributions make it possible for the SPCA to:

* Care for nearly 50,000 domestic, farm and wild animals in need;
* Provide emergency rescue and treatment for thousands of injured animals;
* Carry out nearly 6,000 animal cruelty investigations;
* Advocate higher standards for the 100 million farm animals raised in BC every year, and press for stronger national laws to protect the 600 million farm animals transported throughout Canada;
* Advocate on issues such as rodeos, avian influenza and national farming codes of practice;
* Oversee SPCA Certified, a food labeling program that assures consumers the products they choose are derived from animals that have been raised according to the BC SPCA's high standards of animal welfare;
* Reduce the tragedy of pet overpopulation through low-cost spay/neuter programs across BC;
* Present programs to increase empathy and respect for animals to thousands of BC children through summer camps, the BC SPCA Kids Club and school presentations;
* Advocate for stronger anti-cruelty laws to protect animals from abuse and neglect;
* Provide life-saving rescue and rehabilitation for injured wildlife.

Please visit www.spca.bc.ca/walk/about.shtml for more information or provide help or donations to one of our other MANY SPCA fundraising campaigns.

